At Ilife, we take your privacy seriously. We understand that you trust us to handle your personal information, and we are committed to protecting it. This privacy policy (the \"Policy\") explains how we collect, use, and share your personal information, as well as your rights in relation to your personal information. Collection of Personal Information We may collect personal information from you when you interact with us, such as when you visit our website, create an account, make a purchase, or contact customer support. The types of personal information we may collect include your name, email address, postal address, telephone number, and payment information. Use of Personal Information We use your personal information to provide and improve our products and services, to communicate with you, and to comply with legal obligations. For example, we may use your personal information to: process your orders and deliver the products you have purchased; send you promotional materials and updates on our products and services; respond to your customer service inquiries or requests; detect and prevent fraud or other illegal activities; comply with applicable laws and regulations. Sharing of Personal Information We may share your personal information with third parties in the following circumstances: with our service providers and partners, such as payment processors and shipping companies, to fulfill your orders and provide our services; with law enforcement or other government agencies, as required by law or to protect our rights and the rights of others; with other companies in the event of a merger or acquisition.

Your Rights: You have certain rights in relation to your personal information, including: the right to access your personal information; the right to request the correction or deletion of your personal information; the right to object to the processing of your personal information; the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information; the right to receive your personal information in a portable format; the right to withdraw your consent to the processing of your personal information. We will respond to your requests in accordance with applicable laws. Changes to This Policy We may update this Policy from time to time to reflect changes to our practices or to comply with legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes to this Policy by posting the new Policy on our website. Contact Us If you have any questions or concerns about this Policy or our handling of your personal information, please contact us at privacy@ilife.com.
Ilife is a booking company that provides a platform for users to book appointments with various businesses, such as restaurants, dental clinics, and more.
2. What types of businesses can I book through Ilife?
You can book appointments with various businesses, including restaurants, dental clinics, beauty salons, and more. The selection of businesses will vary depending on your location.
3. How do I book an appointment through Ilife?

To book an appointment through Ilife, simply go to the Ilife website, search for the business you wish to book with, select the date and time that works best for you, and follow the instructions to complete the booking process.
4. Can I make same-day bookings through Ilife?
Yes, Ilife provides the option to make same-day bookings, subject to availability.
5. What happens if I need to cancel or reschedule my appointment?

If you need to cancel or reschedule your appointment, you can do so through the Ilife platform. The cancellation policy for each business may vary, so it is important to review the details before confirming your booking.
6. Is there a fee for using Ilife?
There may be a fee for using Ilife, depending on the business you are booking with. It is important to review the details and any applicable fees before confirming your booking.
